title: Space launch supply chokepoint puts U.S. in vulnerable spot, expert warns
summary: The U.S. government has to face the prospect of having to rely on a single launch provider

title: Historic first launch of Chinese private methane-fueled rocket ends in failure
summary: Chinese launch company Landspace suffered failure Wednesday in what was the world's first attempt to achieve orbit with a methane-fueled rocket.

title: Space debris expert: Orbits will be lost—and people will die—later this decade
summary: "Flexing geopolitical muscles in space to harm others has already happened."

title: Ariane 5 rocket launches new European Meteosat satellite, two Intelsat comsats
summary: A European Ariane 5 rocket fired off a launching stand Tuesday in tropical South America with the vanguard of a modernized series of weather satellites to improve storm forecasts for Europe, Africa, and the Middle East, and two Intelsat television broadcasting satellites to cover the United States, a heavyweight payload totaling 12 tons.

title: First African nations sign Artemis Accords
summary: Two African countries became the first from the continent to join the Artemis Accords as the United States works to bring more emerging space nations into the agreement.
